generate.label: Sampling method
generate.hint: Which algorithm to use to produce the image

generate.label: Steps
generate.hint: How many times to improve the generated image iteratively; higher values take longer; very low values can produce bad results

generate.label: Tiling
generate.hint: Produce an image that can be tiled

generate.label: Full quality
generate.hint: Use full quality VAE to decode latent samples

generate.label: HiDiffusion
generate.hint: HiDiffusion allows creation of high-resolution images using your standard models without duplicates/distortions and improved performance

generate.label: HDR Clamp
generate.hint: Adjusts the level of nonsensical details by pruning values that deviate significantly from the distribution mean. It is particularly useful for enhancing generation at higher guidance scales, identifying outliers early in the process and applying mathematical adjustments based on the Range (Boundary) and Threshold settings. Think of it as setting the range within which you want your image values to be, and adjusting the threshold determines which values should be brought back into that range

generate.label: HDR Maximize
generate.hint: Calculates a 'normalization factor' by dividing the maximum tensor value by the specified range multiplied by 4. This factor is then used to shift the channels within the given boundary, ensuring maximum dynamic range for subsequent processing. The objective is to optimize dynamic range for external applications like Photoshop, particularly for adjusting levels, contrast, and brightness

generate.label: Enable refine pass
generate.hint: Use a similar process as image to image to upscale and/or add detail to the final image. Optionally uses refiner model to enhance image details.

generate.label: Enable detailer pass
generate.hint: Detect target objects such as face and reprocess it at higher resolution

generate.label: Denoising strength
generate.hint: Determines how little respect the algorithm should have for image's content. At 0, nothing will change, and at 1 you'll get an unrelated image. With values below 1.0, processing will take less steps than the Sampling Steps slider specifies

generate.label: Denoise start
generate.hint: Override denoise strength by stating how early base model should finish and when refiner should start. Only applicable to refiner usage. If set to 0 or 1, denoising strength will be used

generate.label: Hires steps
generate.hint: Number of sampling steps for upscaled picture. If 0, uses same as for original

generate.label: Strength
generate.hint: Denoising strength of during image operation controls how much of original image is allowed to change during generate

generate.label: Upscaler
generate.hint: Which pre-trained model to use for the upscaling process.

generate.label: Force Hires
generate.hint: Hires runs automatically when Latent upscale is selected, but its skipped when using non-latent upscalers. Enable force hires to run hires with non-latent upscalers

generate.label: Resize width
generate.hint: Resizes image to this width. If 0, width is inferred from either of two nearby sliders

generate.label: Resize height
generate.hint: Resizes image to this height. If 0, height is inferred from either of two nearby sliders

generate.label: Refine sampler
generate.hint: Use specific sampler as fallback sampler if primary is not supported for specific operation

generate.label: Refiner start
generate.hint: Refiner pass will start when base model is this much complete (set to larger than 0 and smaller than 1 to run after full base model run)

generate.label: Refiner steps
generate.hint: Number of steps to use for refiner pass

generate.label: Refine guidance
generate.hint: CFG scale used for refiner pass

generate.label: Attention guidance
generate.hint: CFG scale used for with PAG: Perturbed-Attention Guidance

generate.label: Adaptive scaling
generate.hint: Adaptive modifier for attention guidance scale

generate.label: Rescale guidance
generate.hint: Rescale CFG generated noise to avoid overexposed images

generate.label: Refine Prompt
generate.hint: Prompt used for both second encoder in base model (if it exists) and for refiner pass (if enabled)

generate.label: Refine negative prompt
generate.hint: Negative prompt used for both second encoder in base model (if it exists) and for refiner pass (if enabled)

generate.label: Width
generate.hint: Image width

generate.label: Height
generate.hint: Image height

generate.label: Batch count
generate.hint: How many batches of images to create (has no impact on generation performance or VRAM usage)

generate.label: Batch size
generate.hint: How many image to create in a single batch (increases generation performance at cost of higher VRAM usage)

generate.label: guidance scale
generate.hint: Classifier Free Guidance scale: how strongly the image should conform to prompt. Lower values produce more creative results, higher values make it follow the prompt more strictly; recommended values between 5-10

generate.label: Guidance End
generate.hint: Ends the effect of CFG and PAG early: A value of 1 acts as normal, 0.5 stops guidance at 50% of steps

generate.label: Initial seed
generate.hint: A value that determines the output of random number generator - if you create an image with same parameters and seed as another image, you'll get the same result

generate.label: Variation
generate.hint: Second seed to be mixed with primary seed

generate.label: Variation strength
generate.hint: How strong of a variation to produce. At 0, there will be no effect. At 1, you will get the complete picture with variation seed (except for ancestral samplers, where you will just get something)

generate.label: Resize seed from width
generate.hint: Make an attempt to produce a picture similar to what would have been produced with same seed at specified resolution

generate.label: Resize seed from height
generate.hint: Make an attempt to produce a picture similar to what would have been produced with same seed at specified resolution

generate.label: Fixed
generate.hint: Resize image to target resolution. Unless height and width match, you will get incorrect aspect ratio

generate.label: scale
generate.hint: Resize image to target scale. If resize fixed width/height are set this option is ignored

generate.label: Crop
generate.hint: Resize the image so that entirety of target resolution is filled with the image. Crop parts that stick out

generate.label: Fill
generate.hint: Resize the image so that entirety of image is inside target resolution. Fill empty space with image's colors

generate.label: Mask blur
generate.hint: How much to blur the mask before processing, in pixels

generate.label: Latent noise
generate.hint: fill it with latent space noise

generate.label: Latent nothing
generate.hint: fill it with latent space zeroes
